<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,754,1157]" pageId="10" pageNumber="43">
Endemic to the Atlantic Forest (
<bibRefCitation author="Sobral, M. &amp; Lucas, E. &amp; Landrum, L. &amp; Soares-Silva, L." box="[527,738,793,819]" pageId="10" pageNumber="43" pagination="352 - 366" refId="ref15003" refString="Sobral, M., Lucas, E., Landrum, L. &amp; Soares-Silva, L. (2009) Myrtaceae. In: Stehmann, J., Forzza, R. C., Salino, A., Sobral, M., Costa, D. P. &amp; Kamino, L. H. Y. Plantas da Floresta Atlantica. Rio de Janeiro, pp 352 - 366." type="book chapter" year="2009">
Sobral 
<emphasis box="[612,671,793,818]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="43">et al.</emphasis>
2009
</bibRefCitation>
) from the northeast to south regions of 
<collectingCountry box="[1204,1275,793,819]" name="Brazil" pageId="10" pageNumber="43">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Sobral, M. &amp; Proenca, C. &amp; Souza, M. &amp; Mazine, F. &amp; Lucas, E." pageId="10" pageNumber="43" refId="ref15080" refString="Sobral, M., Proenca, C., Souza, M., Mazine, F. &amp; Lucas, E. (2010) Myrtaceae. In: Forzza, R. C., Leitman, P. M., Costa, A. F., Carvalho Jr., A. A., Peixoto, A. L., Walter, B. M. T., Bicudo, C., Zappi, D., Costa, D. P., Lleras, E., Martinelli, G., Lima, H. C., Prado, J., Stehmann, J. R., Baumgratz, J. F. A., Pirani, J. R., Sylvestre, L., Maia, L. C., Lohmann, L. G., Queiroz, L. P., Silveira, M., Coelho, M. N., Mamede, M. C., Bastos, M. N. C., Morim, M. P., Barbosa, M. R., Menezes, M., Hopkins, M., Secco, R., Cavalcanti, T. B. &amp; Souza, V. C. Lista de Especies da Flora do Brasil. Jardim Botanico do Rio de Janeiro, Rio de Janeiro. Published on the internet; http: // floradobrasil. jbrj. gov. br / 2010 / FB 010791. Accessed: 5 October 2011." type="url" year="2010">
Sobral 
<emphasis box="[1377,1436,793,818]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="43">et al.</emphasis>
2010
</bibRefCitation>
). In the Northeast, it is cited from the States of 
<collectingRegion box="[761,829,831,857]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="10" pageNumber="43">Bahia</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Sobral, M. &amp; Proenca, C. &amp; Souza, M. &amp; Mazine, F. &amp; Lucas, E." box="[844,1056,831,857]" pageId="10" pageNumber="43" refId="ref15080" refString="Sobral, M., Proenca, C., Souza, M., Mazine, F. &amp; Lucas, E. (2010) Myrtaceae. In: Forzza, R. C., Leitman, P. M., Costa, A. F., Carvalho Jr., A. A., Peixoto, A. L., Walter, B. M. T., Bicudo, C., Zappi, D., Costa, D. P., Lleras, E., Martinelli, G., Lima, H. C., Prado, J., Stehmann, J. R., Baumgratz, J. F. A., Pirani, J. R., Sylvestre, L., Maia, L. C., Lohmann, L. G., Queiroz, L. P., Silveira, M., Coelho, M. N., Mamede, M. C., Bastos, M. N. C., Morim, M. P., Barbosa, M. R., Menezes, M., Hopkins, M., Secco, R., Cavalcanti, T. B. &amp; Souza, V. C. Lista de Especies da Flora do Brasil. Jardim Botanico do Rio de Janeiro, Rio de Janeiro. Published on the internet; http: // floradobrasil. jbrj. gov. br / 2010 / FB 010791. Accessed: 5 October 2011." type="url" year="2010">
Sobral 
<emphasis box="[929,987,831,856]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="43">et al.</emphasis>
2010
</bibRefCitation>
). New records of this species for State of 
<collectingRegion box="[250,398,868,894]" country="Brazil" name="Pernambuco" pageId="10" pageNumber="43">Pernambuco</collectingRegion>
are presented here. This species is considered extinct in the State of 
<collectingRegion box="[1220,1371,868,894]" country="Brazil" name="Pernambuco" pageId="10" pageNumber="43">Pernambuco</collectingRegion>
, with no records in the last 60 years.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="43" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,754,1157]" pageId="10" pageNumber="43">
Trees 
<quantity box="[270,360,943,969]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" metricValueMax="12.0" metricValueMin="6.0" pageId="10" pageNumber="43" unit="m" value="9.0" valueMax="12.0" valueMin="6.0">6–12 m</quantity>
tall. This species differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Martius" authorityYear="1837" box="[721,958,944,969]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Marlierea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="10" pageNumber="43" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="excoriata">
<emphasis box="[721,958,944,969]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="43">Marlierea excoriata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having larger leaves (30–40 × 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.15" metricValueMax="1.3" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="10" pageNumber="43" unit="cm" value="11.5" valueMax="13.0" valueMin="10.0">10–13 cm</quantity>
) and pilose fruit; it differs from other 
<taxonomicName box="[644,821,981,1007]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Myrcia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="10" pageNumber="43" phylum="Magnoliopsida" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[644,728,981,1006]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="43">Myrcia</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
by having the calyx closed in the bud, tearing open irregularly.
</paragraph>
